<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td>
	     <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%" >
	     <form action="/cgi-bin/mrate.pl" name="f107652183231095">
	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=19846&amp;mid=107652183231095">Languages you need.</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=19846&amp;mid=107652183231095#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Wed, Feb 11th 12:50 PM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=163485"><span id=" ">Mordance</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">11 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Unless there is a language out there that you can't get from a trainer, I've got all the languages mastered. I did so exclusively for this charm.<br/><br/>A few things:<br/><br/>- The stats listed in the picture are the highest you can achieve as far as I know. Magelo lists every stat one higher, so there is a language I don't know about, SOE is intentionally leaving room to add more, or there is a snafu in the way the charm should be working. Since there are 10 exotic languages, I'm betting on the snafu.<br/><br/>- Only exotic languages matter, not the PC playable race languages. I was missing over half of the PC races when I got the highest stats that are possible and the charm did not change once I mastered them.<br/><br/>- The exotic languages that I'm fairly certain work on the charm are: Old Erudian, Elder Elvish, Goblin, Gnoll, Combine, Orcish, Elder Tier'Dal, Faerie, Dragon, and Elder Dragon.<br/><br/>- Dark Speech may or not be exotic, but only having mastery of that language and Troll did not affect the charm. If it is an exotic language, you need more than one to get any stats from the charm. Thieves Cant didn't seem to have an effect either.<br/><br/>- From these, I conclude that roughly each of the exotic languages I listed raises the charm's Cha and DR by one point, and every two exotic languages raises the Int/Wis by one point. I wish I had recorded the upgrades with screenshots to conclude this with absolute certainty, but I am reasonably certain that formula is the case.<br/><br/>- I'm reasonably confident there are only 25 languages that are learnable, as Magelo only lists 25 and <a href=HTTP://eqlive.station.sony.com/community/fippy_facts.jsp?id=43096 target=akztarg>Fippy</a> lists 23 (with Common and Vah Shir not listed.)<br/><br/>- I haven't found a definitive link, but I believe Kobold used to be a language in the game, but it was removed from both trainers and players that had learned it.<br/><br/>Hope that helps.<br/><br/>EDIT: Crap, forgot about Orcish.<br/><br/><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Feb 11 13:34:13 2004</em></p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
